name: YamlMap
comment:
This class behaves almost identically to the normal Dart yaml/dart-core.Map implementation, with the following differences:

  • It allows NaN, list, and map keys.

  • It defines == structurally. That is, yamlMap1 == yamlMap2 if they have the same contents.

  • It has a compatible yaml/yaml.YamlMap.hashCode method.

This class is deprecated. In future releases, this package will use a yaml/dart-collection.HashMap with a custom equality operation rather than a custom class.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides yaml/yaml.YamlMap.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and yaml/yaml.YamlMap.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the yaml/yaml.YamlMap.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

hashCode.comment:

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no key-value pair in the map.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one key-value pair in the map.

keys.name: keys
keys.comment:
The keys of this.

The returned iterable has efficient length and contains operations, based on yaml/yaml.YamlMap.length and yaml/yaml.YamlMap.containsKey of the map.

The order of iteration is defined by the individual Map implementation, but must be consistent between changes to the map.

length.name: length
length.comment: The number of key-value pairs in the map.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

values.name: values
values.comment:
The values of this.

The values are iterated in the order of their corresponding keys. This means that iterating yaml/yaml.YamlMap.keys and yaml/yaml.YamlMap.values in parrallel will provided matching pairs of keys and values.

The returned iterable has an efficient length method based on the yaml/yaml.YamlMap.length of the map.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and yaml/yaml.YamlMap.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the yaml/yaml.YamlMap.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

[].comment: Returns the value for the given yaml/yaml.YamlMap.[].key or null if yaml/yaml.YamlMap.[].key is not in the map. Because null values are supported, one should either use yaml/yaml.YamlMap.containsKey to distinguish between an absent key and a null value, or use the yaml/yaml.YamlMap.putIfAbsent method.

[]=.comment:
Associates the yaml/yaml.YamlMap.[]=.key with the given yaml/yaml.YamlMap.[]=.value.

If the key was already in the map, its associated value is changed. Otherwise the key-value pair is added to the map.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment:
Adds all key-value pairs of yaml/yaml.YamlMap.addAll.other to this map.

If a key of yaml/yaml.YamlMap.addAll.other is already in this map, its value is overwritten.

The operation is equivalent to doing this[key] = value for each key and associated value in other. It iterates over yaml/yaml.YamlMap.addAll.other, which must therefore not change during the iteration.

clear.name: clear
clear.comment:
Removes all pairs from the map.

After this, the map is empty.

containsKey.name: containsKey
containsKey.comment: Returns true if this map contains the given key.

containsValue.name: containsValue
containsValue.comment: Returns true if this map contains the given value.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment:
Applies yaml/yaml.YamlMap.forEach.f to each {key, value} pair of the map.

Adding or removing keys from the map during iteration is not allowed.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
yaml/yaml.YamlMap.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to yaml/yaml.YamlMap.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If yaml/yaml.YamlMap.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of yaml/yaml.YamlMap.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

putIfAbsent.name: putIfAbsent
putIfAbsent.comment:
If yaml/yaml.YamlMap.putIfAbsent.key is not associated to a value, calls yaml/yaml.YamlMap.putIfAbsent.ifAbsent and updates the map by mapping yaml/yaml.YamlMap.putIfAbsent.key to the value returned by yaml/yaml.YamlMap.putIfAbsent.ifAbsent. Returns the value in the map.

Map<String, int> scores = {'Bob': 36};
for (var key in ['Bob', 'Rohan', 'Sophena']) {
  scores.putIfAbsent(key, () => key.length);
}
scores['Bob'];      // 36
scores['Rohan'];    //  5
scores['Sophena'];  //  7

The code that yaml/yaml.YamlMap.putIfAbsent.ifAbsent executes must not add or remove keys.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment: Removes the association for the given yaml/yaml.YamlMap.remove.key. Returns the value for yaml/yaml.YamlMap.remove.key in the map or null if yaml/yaml.YamlMap.remove.key is not in the map. Note that values can be null and a returned null value does not always imply that the key is absent.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.
